$\epsilon_i$ denotes a random energy shift at the $i$th site.   In our study, the disorder is uniformly distributed with $\epsilon_i\in\{-\Delta/2,\Delta/2\}$.  Specifically, we use the box probability distribution function:
 \begin{eqnarray}
  P(\epsilon)=\frac{\Theta \left(\Delta-\vert\epsilon\vert \right)}{2\Delta},
   \label{eq_PU}
 \end{eqnarray}
where $\Delta$ is the strength of the disorder and $\Theta$ is the Heaviside step function. 

